'''Ozan Muhammed Kabak''' (born 25 March 2000) is a [[Turkish]] [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[Bundesliga]] club [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|TSG Hoffenheim]] and the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]].

==Club career==
===Galatasaray===
Ozan trained with the [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]] youth academy, joining in 2011. He signed his first professional contract with Galatasaray on 1 July 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://skor.sozcu.com.tr/2018/05/13/galatasarayda-bir-ilk-ozan-kabak-727287/|title=Galatasaray'da bir ilk… Ozan Kabak…}}</ref> Ozan made his professional debut for Galatasaray in a 2–0 [[Süper Lig]] win over [[Yeni Malatyaspor]] on 12 May 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=29&macId=180627|title=GALATASARAY A.Ş. EVKUR YENİ MALATYASPOR - Maç Detayları TFF|website=www.tff.org}}</ref> This made him the first footballer born in the 2000s to play in the Süper Lig.<ref>{{cite web |date=25 September 2022 |title=Ozan Kabak - Ansiklopedika Viki |url=https://tr.ansiklopedika.net/viki/ozan-kabak,%20https://tr.ansiklopedika.net/viki/ozan-kabak |access-date=25 September 2022 |language=tr}}</ref> On 24 October 2018, he played his first [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] match in a 0–0 home draw against [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]] in the [[2018–19 UEFA Champions League|2018–19 season]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2025100--galatasaray-vs-schalke/?referrer=%2Fuefachampionsleague%2Fseason%3D2019%2Fmatches%2Fround%3D2000980%2Fmatch%3D2025100%2Findex |title=Galatasaray 0–0 Schalke |website=UEFA |date=24 October 2018 }}</ref>

===VfB Stuttgart===
On 17 January 2019, Kabak moved to [[Bundesliga]] side [[VfB Stuttgart]] where he signed a contract until June 2024.<ref>{{cite news|title=VfB sign Ozan Kabak|url=https://www.vfb.de/en/vfb/latest/news/professionals/2019/verpflichtung-ozan-kabak/|access-date=17 January 2019|publisher=VfB Stuttgart|date=17 January 2019}}</ref> On 3 March, he scored twice in a 5–1 win over [[Hannover 96]], registering his first senior  career goals.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mario Gomez, Ozan Kabak and Steven Zuber fire VfB Stuttgart to victory in relegation six-pointer with Hannover|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/vfb-stuttgart-hannover-live-line-ups-stats-pavard-mario-gomez-bobby-wood-2673|access-date=3 March 2019|publisher=Bundesliga|date=3 March 2019}}</ref> In doing so, at the age of 18 years, 11 months and 7 days, he became the youngest Turkish center-back, and third-youngest Stuttgart player to ever score twice in a single Bundesliga match.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/ozan-kabak-schalke-s-rising-defensive-star-turkey-van-dijk-ramos-3859|title=Ozan Kabak: Who is VfB Stuttgart's rising defensive star?|publisher=Bundesliga|date=18 April 2019|access-date=21 April 2019}}</ref>

===Schalke 04===
On 30 June 2019, Kabak joined [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]] on a five-year contract for a fee of €15 million, after Schalke activated a [[Buyout clause|release clause]] in his contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://schalke04.de/en/team/fc-schalke-04-sign-ozan-kabak-stuttgart/|title=FC Schalke 04 sign Ozan Kabak from Stuttgart|date=30 June 2019|publisher=[[FC Schalke 04]]}}</ref> He was a regular performer in his first season with the club, appearing in 28 matches and scoring three goals.<ref>{{Cite news |title=AC Milan considering a €25 million offer for Liverpool target Ozan Kabak |url=https://footballexpress.in/ac-milan-transfer-offer-liverpool-target-ozan-kabak/ |website=footballexpress.in |date=3 December 2020 |access-date=16 December 2020 |archive-date=16 December 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201216104045/https://footballexpress.in/ac-milan-transfer-offer-liverpool-target-ozan-kabak/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> In September 2020, he was banned for five games and hit with a €15,000 fine after being caught spitting at [[Werder Bremen]]'s [[Ludwig Augustinsson]]. Kabak apologised to Augustinsson via Twitter afterwards, insisting the incident, for which he was shown a red card, was an accident.<ref>{{Cite web|title= Liverpool complete loan deal for Schalke defender Ozan Kabak |url= https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/liverpool-complete-loan-deal-for-schalke-defender-ozan-kabak/tjxa7dz71ule1vxesvzt3qope|website=Goal.com |date=2 February 2021}}</ref>

====Liverpool (loan)====
On 1 February 2021, Kabak signed for [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] on loan for the remainder of the [[2020–21 Liverpool F.C. season|2020–21 season]]. The deal was reportedly worth £1 million, plus potentially £500,000 in add-ons depending on appearances and Liverpool's performance in the Champions League. It also included an option to buy, which was set at approximately £18 million and could rise to £26.5m with add-ons.<ref>{{Cite web|title= Liverpool sign Ozan Kabak on loan from Schalke|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/liverpool/ozan-kabak-transfer-news-loan-b1795985.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220524/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/liverpool/ozan-kabak-transfer-news-loan-b1795985.html |archive-date=2022-05-24 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live|access-date=2021-02-02|website=Independent.co.uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.skysports.com/football/news/12040/12205717/ozan-kabak-transfer-liverpool-agree-deal-for-schalke-centre-back-as-arsenal-defender-shkodran-mustafi-set-to-join-bundesliga-club|title= Ozan Kabak transfer: Liverpool agree deal for Schalke centre-back as Arsenal defender Shkodran Mustafi set to join Bundesliga club|website=Skysports.com|date=1 February 2021|access-date=2 February 2021}}</ref> On 13 February 2021, he made his Liverpool debut in a [[2020–21 Premier League|Premier League]] game against [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]], ending in a 1–3 away defeat.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/first-team/425606-confirmed-team-news-leicester-premier-league |title=Team news: Confirmed Liverpool line-up v Leicester |first=James |last=Carroll |publisher=Liverpool FC |date=13 February 2021 |accessdate=13 February 2021}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Phil |last=McNulty |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/55960005 |title=Leicester 3-1 Liverpool: Foxes take advantage of late defensive errors |website=[[BBC Sport]] |date=13 February 2021 |access-date=13 February 2021}}</ref> On 16 February, he played in a 2–0 away win over [[RB Leipzig]] in the [[2020–21 UEFA Champions League]], becoming the first Turkish player to appear for an English club in the competition.<ref>{{cite tweet |user=ChampionsLeague |title=Ozan Kabak becomes the first Turkish player to appear for an English club in the Champions League |number=1361781887262408710 |date=16 February 2021 }}</ref> At the end of the season, Liverpool declined to sign Kabak on a permanent basis.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/57242659 |title=Ibrahima Konate: Liverpool agree to sign RB Leipzig defender for £35m on long-term deal|website=[[BBC Sport]] |date=28 May 2021 |access-date=28 May 2021}}</ref>

====Norwich City (loan)====
On 30 August 2021, Kabak returned to England to join newly promoted [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] on a season-long loan deal with the club having an option to make the deal permanent at the end of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.canaries.co.uk/News/2021/august/city-complete-signing-of-ozan-kabak/|title=City complete signing of Ozan Kabak|website=www.canaries.co.uk|date=30 August 2021}}</ref>

=== TSG Hoffenheim ===
On 23 July 2022, Kabak moved to [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|TSG Hoffenheim]] and signed a contract until 30 June 2026. He also has a clause where it shows he could earn up to 8 million in add ons.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.tsg-hoffenheim.de/aktuelles/news/2022/07/kabak-staerkt-die-tsg-defensive/ |title=Kabak stärkt die TSG-Defensive |trans-title=Kabak strengthens the TSG defense |language=de |website=tsg-hoffenheim.de |publisher=TSG Hoffenheim |date=23 July 2022 |access-date=23 July 2022}}</ref>

==International career==
Ozan is a youth international for Turkey. He captained the [[Turkey national under-17 football team|Turkey U17]]s at the [[2017 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fanatik.com.tr/2018/05/12/ozan-kabak-kimdir-1370734|title=Ozan Kabak kimdir?|last=fanatik|website=Fanatik}}</ref> and was listed as one of the 10 players to watch by [[UEFA]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/under17/news/0252-0cda41f910d9-58c34a2eab80-1000--ten-to-watch-from-u17-euro-in-croatia/|title=Under-17 - News – UEFA.com|last=uefa.com|date=22 May 2017}}</ref>

On 17 November 2019, Kabak made his debut in the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey senior team]] during the team's [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying]] match against [[Andorra national football team|Andorra]], playing the full match which Turkey won 2–0.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ozan Kabak and Ahmed Kutucu celebrate debut win |url=https://schalke04.de/en/internationals/ozan-kabak-ahmed-kutucu-celebrate-debut-win/ |publisher=FC Schalke 04 |access-date=10 January 2020 |date=17 November 2019}}</ref> Kabak scored his first international goal on 16 November 2022 in a 2–1 friendly win over [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Ramsay debuts, Robertson assists and ex-LFC loanee scores in mid-season friendly |url=https://www.thisisanfield.com/2022/11/ramsay-debuts-robertson-assists-and-ex-lfc-loanee-scores-in-mid-season-friendly/ |website=This is Anfield |access-date=17 November 2022}}</ref>

On 24 May 2024, Kabak was named in the 35-man preliminary squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |date=24 May 2024 |title=A Millî Takımımızın EURO 2024 Geniş Kadrosu Açıklandı |trans-title=EURO 2024 squad of our national team announced |url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=44364 |language=tr |publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]] |access-date=30 May 2024}}</ref> On 5 June, he was withdrawn due to knee injury prior to the tournament.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ozan Kabak'ın Sağlık Durumu Hakkında Bilgilendirme - A Milli Takım Haber Detayları TFF |url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=44534 |website=www.tff.org |publisher=Turkish Football Federation |access-date=5 June 2024 |language=tr}}</ref>

